SpotImporter([parent])

A dialog for importing spot data into LaME
class app.SpotImporter.SpotImporter(parent=None)[source]#

Bases: QDialog, Ui_SpotImportDialog

A dialog for importing spot data into LaME

Import spot data. Import format requires csv file(s) with one row per spot and columns with metadata and analyses.

add_combobox(col)[source]#

Adds a combobox with column data types to the first row.

The user can use the combobox to select the type of data given column. These types are used to develop a standard format for importing into LaME. An attempt is made to determine the type, but the user will need to verify.

Parameters:

col (int) – Column to add the combobox to

import_spot_table()[source]#

Update the MainWindow.tableWidgetSpots and update MainWindow.spot_data

Add spot data to LaME when pushButtonImport is clicked.

insert_column(currentColumn)[source]#

Insert a column into tableWidgetSpotData

Parameters:

currentColumn (int) – Column to rename

load_spot_data()[source]#

Load spot data file(s) when toolButtonOpenSpotFile

Loads csv data into tableWidgetSpotData for the user to view and update before importing. A row of comboboxes are added to the first row that defines the type of column data. An attempt is made to determine the type, but the user will need to verify.
